---
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Topnav from "../components/Topnav.astro";
import { inversion, tenets } from "../data/manifesto";
import { RECEIPTS } from "../data/research-receipts";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

// Long-form manifesto (redesign-plan §5 /manifesto). Editorial moment:
// single 720px column, display serif at 400 for running text, drop cap
// on the opening paragraph, smallcaps via <abbr> for cited entities,
// pull-quotes at --t-section with lime hairline rules. No hard-shadow
// boxes — the page IS the rhythm. Lime only on pull-quote hairlines
// and the closing CTA. ResearchReceipts content is folded in below as
// a "Receipts" section (each receipt is a citation, not a card).
---

<Base
  title="Manifesto — nlqdb"
  description="Nine non-negotiables that decide every nlqdb design choice. A database you talk to, with a backend that doesn't exist."
  canonical="/manifesto"
>
  <div class="page">
    <Topnav current="manifesto" />

    <main class="m">
      <header class="m-head">
        <p class="m-kicker">Manifesto</p>
        <h1 class="m-title">
          A database you talk to,<br />
          with a backend that doesn&rsquo;t exist.
        </h1>
      </header>

      <div class="m-prose">
        <p class="m-lede">
          <span class="m-dropcap">N</span>lqdb is a natural-language database:
          you create one with a name, you query it in English, and the schema,
          the engine, the indexes, the migrations and the cache are all
          background concerns you never have to see. What follows is the bar
          every change is judged against. If a change violates one of these,
          it doesn&rsquo;t ship. Not as guidelines &mdash; as acceptance
          criteria.
        </p>

        <blockquote class="m-pull">
          What is nlqdb? A database that accepts natural language as its
          query language, picks the right engine for your workload &mdash;
          <abbr title="Postgres">Postgres</abbr>,
          <abbr title="ClickHouse">ClickHouse</abbr>,
          <abbr title="Redis">Redis</abbr> &mdash; and exposes itself through
          five surfaces: an <abbr title="HTML">HTML</abbr> element, a typed
          <abbr title="Software Development Kit">SDK</abbr>, a
          <abbr title="Command Line Interface">CLI</abbr>, an
          <abbr title="Model Context Protocol">MCP</abbr> server, and a chat
          web app &mdash; all backed by the same engine.
        </blockquote>

        <p>
          The free tier is the same engine paying customers run on; the
          escape hatch to raw <abbr title="Structured Query Language">SQL</abbr>
          stays one click away, always.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ol class="m-tenets">
        {
          tenets.map((t) => (
            <li class="m-tenet">
              <p class="m-tenet-num">{t.n}</p>
              <h2 class="m-tenet-title">{t.title}</h2>
              <div class="m-tenet-body">
                {t.body.map((p) => (
                  <p>{p}</p>
                ))}
              </div>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ol>

      <section class="m-section" aria-labelledby="inversion-title">
        <h2 class="m-h2" id="inversion-title">The on-ramp inversion.</h2>
        <p>
          The single most important design decision: every entry point
          accepts <em>a goal</em>, not a database name. Every surface,
          reframed.
        </p>

        <div class="m-table-wrap">
          <table class="m-table">
            <caption class="m-table-cap">
              Surface-by-surface inversion of the first action.
            </caption>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Surface</th>
                <th scope="col">Old &mdash; DB-first</th>
                <th scope="col">New &mdash; goal-first</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {
                inversion.map((row) => (
                  <tr>
                    <th scope="row">{row.surface}</th>
                    <td set:html={row.oldHtml} />
                    <td set:html={row.newHtml} />
                  </tr>
                ))
              }
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="m-section" aria-labelledby="not-title">
        <h2 class="m-h2" id="not-title">What this isn&rsquo;t.</h2>
        <dl class="m-not">
          <div class="m-not-row">
            <dt>Not a SQL builder.</dt>
            <dd>
              There is no &ldquo;here is your generated SQL, paste it into
              your <abbr title="Object-Relational Mapper">ORM</abbr>&rdquo;
              step.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="m-not-row">
            <dt>Not a vector store with a wrapper.</dt>
            <dd>
              <abbr title="Postgres">Postgres</abbr> with
              <abbr title="pgvector">pgvector</abbr> is one of the engines
              under the hood, not the product.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="m-not-row">
            <dt>Not a chat-on-top-of-your-warehouse layer.</dt>
            <dd>
              We own the storage too. Otherwise schema, indexes and
              migrations leak back into the user&rsquo;s brain.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="m-not-row">
            <dt>Not a no-code tool.</dt>
            <dd>
              The whole point is that developers stay in their editor, in
              their language, against their build. nlqdb is a backend, not
              a <abbr title="Graphical User Interface">GUI</abbr>.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section class="m-section" aria-labelledby="receipts-title">
        <h2 class="m-h2" id="receipts-title">Receipts.</h2>
        <p>
          A pre-alpha making technical claims has to show its work. Each
          design call below is anchored to a paper, postmortem, or
          production system that taught us the lesson.
        </p>

        <ol class="m-receipts">
          {
            RECEIPTS.map((r) => (
              <li class="m-receipt">
                <h3 class="m-receipt-lesson">{r.lesson}</h3>
                <p class="m-receipt-why">{r.why}</p>
                <p class="m-receipt-cite">
                  <a
                    class="m-receipt-src"
                    href={r.url}
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  >
                    {r.source}
                  </a>
                  <span class="m-receipt-applied">
                    Applied at <span class="m-receipt-loc">{r.appliedAt.label}</span>.
                  </span>
                </p>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ol>
      </section>

      <p class="m-cta-wrap">
        <a class="cta" href="/">Back to the snippet</a>
      </p>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  /* /manifesto — editorial long-form moment (redesign-plan §5).
     Single 720px measure, Source Serif 4 at body weight 400 for running
     text. Drop cap on the opening paragraph. <abbr> rendered as
     smallcaps. Pull-quotes at --t-section with lime hairline rules.
     No hard-shadow boxes anywhere; the page is the rhythm. */

  .m {
    max-width: var(--col);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(56px, 9vw, 96px) 0 clamp(56px, 8vw, 96px);
    font-family: var(--display);
    color: var(--body);
  }

  .m-head {
    margin-bottom: clamp(48px, 7vw, 72px);
  }

  .m-kicker {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: var(--t-small);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .m-title {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: var(--t-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-wrap: balance;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .m-prose {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(48px, 7vw, 72px);
  }

  .m-prose p {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: var(--t-large);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--body);
    margin: 0 0 1.2em;
  }

  .m-prose p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .m-lede {
    font-size: var(--t-large);
  }

  .m-dropcap {
    float: left;
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 4.4em;
    line-height: 0.85;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0.06em 0.08em 0 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  /* Pull-quote — section-sized type, lime hairline rules above + below.
     This is the only place lime appears on the page apart from the
     closing CTA. */
  .m-pull {
    margin: clamp(40px, 6vw, 56px) 0;
    padding: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--t-section);
    line-height: 1.18;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .m-pull abbr {
    font-style: normal;
  }

  /* Smallcaps for cited entities. font-variant-caps:all-small-caps gets
     true smallcaps from Source Serif 4 where supported, falling back
     to scale+uppercase elsewhere. No underline (the default UA <abbr>
     dotted underline reads as noise here). */
  abbr[title] {
    font-variant-caps: all-small-caps;
    font-feature-settings: "smcp", "c2sc";
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 0;
    cursor: help;
  }

  /* Numbered tenets — no card chrome. Numeral as mono eyebrow,
     title as display, body as display 400 running text. */
  .m-tenets {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 0 clamp(48px, 7vw, 72px);
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(40px, 6vw, 56px);
  }

  .m-tenet {
    padding: 0;
    border: 0;
    background: transparent;
  }

  .m-tenet-num {
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: var(--t-small);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .m-tenet-title {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: var(--t-section);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .m-tenet-body p {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: var(--t-large);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--body);
    margin: 0 0 0.9em;
  }

  .m-tenet-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Generic section (inversion, not-list, receipts). */
  .m-section {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(48px, 7vw, 72px);
  }

  .m-section > p {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: var(--t-large);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--body);
    margin: 0 0 clamp(24px, 3vw, 32px);
  }

  .m-h2 {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: var(--t-section);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }

  /* Inversion table — hairline rules only, no surrounding card. */
  .m-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .m-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--t-body);
    text-align: left;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  .m-table-cap {
    caption-side: top;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0 0 14px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: var(--t-small);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .m-table th,
  .m-table td {
    padding: 14px 16px 14px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    vertical-align: top;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .m-table thead th {
    color: var(--muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-size: var(--t-small);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    padding-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .m-table tbody tr:last-child th,
  .m-table tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .m-table th[scope="row"] {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .m-table code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.92em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .m-table thead {
      display: none;
    }
    .m-table,
    .m-table tbody,
    .m-table tr {
      display: block;
    }
    .m-table tr {
      padding: 14px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .m-table tr:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
    }
    .m-table th[scope="row"] {
      display: block;
      padding: 0 0 6px;
      border-bottom: none;
    }
    .m-table td {
      display: block;
      padding: 2px 0;
      border-bottom: none;
    }
  }

  /* "What this isn't" — definition list, hairline-separated. */
  .m-not {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .m-not-row {
    padding: 18px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .m-not-row:first-child {
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .m-not-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .m-not dt {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--t-large);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 6px;
  }

  .m-not dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: var(--t-large);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  /* Receipts — each one a citation, not a card. Hairline-separated,
     source name as the link, applied-at as a mono footer. */
  .m-receipts {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .m-receipt {
    padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .m-receipt:first-child {
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .m-receipt:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .m-receipt-lesson {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--t-large);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }

  .m-receipt-why {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: var(--t-body);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--body);
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }

  .m-receipt-cite {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px 16px;
    align-items: baseline;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: var(--t-small);
  }

  .m-receipt-src {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--rule);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .m-receipt-src:hover {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration-color: var(--ink);
  }

  .m-receipt-applied {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .m-receipt-loc {
    color: var(--body);
  }

  /* Closing CTA — lime moment, the only one on the page besides the
     pull-quote hairlines. */
  .m-cta-wrap {
    margin: clamp(56px, 8vw, 80px) 0 0;
    padding-top: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    text-align: left;
  }
</style>
</Base>
